******
[2] Tamil Nadu, dairy industry
Date: Wed 4 Dec 2013
Source: Press Trust of India (PTI) [edited]
http://www.ptinews.com/news/4203344_Milk-production-hit-in-TN-by-foot-and-mouth-disease.html


The current outbreak of FMD among cattle has significantly hit milk production in Tamil Nadu, prompting dairy farmers to seek intervention, including large scale vaccination.

The daily procurement [of milk] has come down by about 4 lakh [400 000] litres a day, according to Tamil Nadu Milk Producers' Welfare Association (TNMPWA) President K A Sengottuvel.

